$interpreted: Yan-Bo: The clouds come and go, while flowers fall like snow...
Law: Enough already! I'm in a good mood, please do not ruin it with your poems.
Yan-Bo: Ah...
Pang: ...So, Master Yan-Bo, was it Law that convinced you to come back?
Law: Hmph! If it were not for Yan-Bo running away to distant lands all those years ago, letting Sennosuke get off scot-free...
Law: Then maybe Sennosuke would not be the scoundrel he is today!
Yan-Bo: ...When I left the east, I put all of those quarrels behind me. That is, until an old friend came to Maple Lake and told me—
Law: You reap what you sow!
Yan-Bo: Ah yes, and it echoed through my mind like a morning bell.
Yan-Bo: Now it is time for me to come to terms with it all.
Jia-Shen: Well, you two breakin' in to Sennosuke's hideout and bustin' out Yota, dang that was wild!
Maeok: Thank you two for dealing with Sennosuke... I should have dealt with him long ago. Really, thank you, on behalf of the whole Alliance.
Law: We are friends, there is no reason to thank us or feel guilty. But if you really feel bad, then... well, what do you think, Yan-Bo?
Yan-Bo: The usual.
Maeok: ......
Maeok: ...Okay! The usual!
Law: Hah! There's the Kong Maeok we know and love!
Pang: Master Yan-Bo, this Tiger Tribe talisman... is it really yours...?
Maeok: Master Yan-bo, I don't think that is truly the Tiger Tribe holy talisman, I think it's...
Yan-Bo: ...I knew you would figure it out.
Pang: Eh? What is it, then?
Yan-Bo: It is the Capybara Tribe's holy talisman. I just never returned it to the Alliance.
Pang: The capybara have their own holy talisman!?
Maeok: You were still an infant when the Capybara Tribe was slaughtered, it's no wonder you're not aware.
Law: The Capybara were once a great tribe within the Alliance, up until...
Yan-Bo: Back then, in my efforts to win the holy talisman, I slipped up and in my error fatally wounded Sennosuke's master, Kaito.
Yan-Bo: My actions led to the fall of my entire tribe, and yet I did nothing to stop Sennosuke.
Yan-Bo: I only ran away, a coward...
Pang: Master Yan-Bo...
Yan-Bo: And now this talisman has stuck with me, like a reminder...
Yan-Bo: I gave it to you, hoping that when Maeok saw it, it would stir something in her, and she would help you.
Yan-Bo: And yet, since the holy talismans all look the same, it seems to have been mistaken as belonging to the Tiger Tribe.
Pang: (If that's the case, then what is the meaning of Yao's note...?)

Law: And what a stroke of luck that was!
By the way, Pang, how are those two friends of yours?
Yan-Bo: Old friends, old friends~
Yan-Bo: Yes, I am not sure where the real tiger talisman is, but these things come and go, and correct themselves with time~
Yan-Bo: I think it is about time I go back to Maple Lake.
Pang: You are going back!?
Yan-Bo: I am! I have entrusted Sharice with looking after the lake in my absence, but I'm afraid I should really get back there myself.
Pang: Sharice, huh?
Yan-Bo: That child pretends like she is not worried, then runs over and asks me every day if I've heard any news about you all.
Yan-Bo: She's a good kid, that Sharice.
Pang: Well, then please apologize to her for—
Pang: ...No, actually, I will apologize to her myself on my return.
Yan-Bo: Very good!
Soohyeon: Hi Mr. Law, Mr. Yan-Bo, Mom~
Soohyeon: It's getting late, I should be bringing Mr. Pang and Jia-Shen back to their rooms.
Law: Well isn't Soohyeon a nice girl! How about Miranda and Yota?
Soohyeon: Please don't worry, Mr. Law. The Alliance is scheduling a time for you to go see them yourself.
Pang: Well, then, Master Yan-Bo and I will—
Jia-Shen: Now hold on! Those three haven't seen each other in a long time now, they've definitely got a lot to talk about...
Pang: ...Well then, we should probably be leaving.
Soohyeon: I've brought some wine and snacks for everyone~
Law: Ah, how long has it been since us three could chat over drinks like this?
Yan-Bo: I would say about twenty-two years.
Maeok: ...Twenty-three years, actually.
Maeok: You left twenty-three years ago, Yan-Bo.
Yan-Bo: ...I heard from Law that you all searched for me for quite some time.
Maeok: Of course we did! I...
Maeok: I was even mad at you for a bit. I was going to really give you a piece of my mind if I ever saw you again, but...
Maeok: I'm old now, and it's getting tougher and tougher to have reunions like this. Plus, you've been gone for twenty-three years...
Maeok: So I've left behind that anger. All I want to do now is have a good chat with my friends.
Maeok: Yan-Bo, I was thinking that after the new arbiter takes over, I could pay a visit to you at Maple Lake.
Yan-Bo: Of course! Maple Lake is pretty as a picturebook... After I started living there, I could only think of how much you and Law would love it.
Law: It is quite striking, that Maple Lake. I remember the first time I went there, when Yan-Bo and I were walking along the water...
